  "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7404885926641963008/",
  "preview": "\"Yes, you told me. I just didn't do it.\" That's AI responding to your carefully crafted instructions. You write a beautiful prompt. Clear rules. Principles. Step-by-step logic. AI executes maybe half.",
  "text": "\"𝒀𝒆𝒔, 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒕𝒐𝒍𝒅 𝒎𝒆. 𝑰 𝒋𝒖𝒔𝒕 𝒅𝒊𝒅𝒏'𝒕 𝒅𝒐 𝒊𝒕.\"\nThat's AI responding to your carefully crafted instructions 🙃\n\n\nYou write a beautiful prompt. Clear rules. Principles. Step-by-step logic.\nAI executes maybe half. The other half? Ignored.\nYou ask: \"𝘋𝘪𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘐 𝘵𝘦𝘭𝘭 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘸𝘳𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴?\"\nAnd it goes: \"𝘠𝘦𝘢𝘩, 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘥𝘪𝘥.\" 🤷\n\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮 𝗯𝘂𝗴. 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝘀. 𝗜𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝗲𝘀 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗶𝘁𝘆.\n\n\nFollowing your checklist? Not what this flower was raised for 🌸\n\n\nHere's what I see people do: they try to make AI execute complex sequential workflows.\nAI fails.\nThey get frustrated.\nThey try to approach it as classic programming by adding more and more instructions: \"CRITICAL\", \"IMPORTANT\".\nBoth paths miss the point.\n\n\nThink about what individual productivity is coming from.\nDaily rituals: wake up at the same time every day. Make the bed. Brush teeth. Then rest. Rigidity.\nInside the rigid web, it contains rituals with space for creativity: a 2-hour coding session, a 2-hour brainstorming. And then reflect on your day before going to bed.\n\n\nAs James Clear puts it in Atomic Habits, the rigidity saves you from decision fatigue and turns creativity into repeatable productivity.\n\n\n𝗦𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 + 𝘀𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗲 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗻𝗲𝘄.\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗻𝘀 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗼 𝗿𝗲𝗽𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗶𝘁𝘆.\n𝗦𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺𝘀.\n\n\nClassical algorithms are dumb but obedient.\nThey fail on any unexpectedness and can't create anything new.\nBut 100% reliable and repeatable, you always know what to expect.\nAI is flexible but unreliable.\nIt will surprise you. Sometimes brilliantly. Sometimes terribly 🎰\n\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗹𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻: 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘀𝗰𝗶𝗼𝘂𝘀 𝘀𝘆𝗻𝘁𝗵𝗲𝘀𝗶𝘀 — 𝗿𝗶𝗴𝗶𝗱 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺𝘀 + 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗔𝗜.\n\n\nBuild an orchestrator.\nStep A, step B. If step B returns X, repeat step A; otherwise, do step C.\nNo step left, no step right.\nUse AI inside the step, don't allow AI to decide what to do next: A or C.\n\n\nDon't try to put everything on AI's shoulders; it is flexible but not repeatable.\nDon't try to avoid using AI at all; algorithms are repeatable but not flexible.\nReal results come from deliberately combining both 🔧",
